First Lady Melania Trump addressed over 500 youth at the Community Anti-Drug Coalitions of America (CADCA) Leadership Forum. The forum focuses on substance abuse prevention and training young adults to be leaders in their communities. Mrs. Trump spoke about the importance of their training sessions and the power of their individual voices. She also presented awards to recipients of CADCA's "Agent of Change" and "Mentorship and Legacy" awards. Following the forum, Mrs. Trump received a policy briefing on the nation's opioid epidemic and participated in a conversation about programs and treatment facilities for young mothers and children suffering from substance abuse. She emphasized the need to educate parents and communities about the dangers of substance abuse.